Name: supravalvular aortic stenosis
Definition: An aortic valve stenosis that is characterized by a narrowing of the section of the aorta just above the valve that connects the aorta to the heart.

Name: subvalvular aortic stenosis
Definition: An aortic valve stenosis that is characterized by a narrowing of the section of the heart under the aortic valve resulting in left ventricular outflow obstruction.
